IN THE HIGH COURT OF RAJASTHAN AT JODHPUR
SECTION 34 / SECTION 36 APPLICATION NO. _______ / 2026

IN THE MATTER OF THE ARBITRAL AWARD DATED 15.11.2026

M/s. Rajputana Builders Pvt. Ltd.                        ...Decree Holder / Respondent
VERSUS
Rajasthan Medical Services Corporation Ltd.              ...Judgment Debtor / Petitioner

APPLICATION FOR STAY OF EXECUTION OF AWARD UNDER SECTION 36(3) OF
THE ARBITRATION AND CONCILIATION ACT, 1996

GROUNDS FOR STAY (RMSCL's Application — filed by Respondent):

1. Award suffers from patent illegality — Claim No. 5 (Loss of Profit) allowed using Hudson
   Formula without adequate evidence of actual profit margin.
2. Price escalation (Claim 3) computed on incorrect base date.
3. Excess jurisdiction — arbitrator granted EOT without express power in contract.

CONTRACTOR'S REPLY TO STAY APPLICATION:

1. Section 36(3): Court must impose condition for depositing award amount if stay is granted.
2. Per NHAI v. M. Hakeem (2021) 9 SCC 1, Section 34 has limited scope — patent illegality
   must go to the root of the award, not mere error of law.
3. Per Batliboi v. Hind Rectifiers, stay of award should not be routine — financial prejudice
   to decree holder must be considered.

PRAYER (Contractor's Counter-Prayer):
Direct RMSCL to deposit 75% of awarded amount (₹13.58 Crore) as pre-condition of stay,
with remaining amount secured by Bank Guarantee.
